I'm going to tell them I lied.

38:02.906 --> 38:04.449
You can't do that, Amy.

38:05.158 --> 38:06.367
We have to stick together.

38:06.451 --> 38:08.578
I'm going to tell them
that the photo was Asha.

38:09.370 --> 38:13.082
And that Mommy made Tamsin steal her
and that you drove the van.

38:19.172 --> 38:21.090
-You can't say that.
-I can.

38:24.636 --> 38:25.678
Fine.

38:29.015 --> 38:31.643
Then when Mommy comes to get me,
I'll tell her what you said,

38:31.726 --> 38:33.186
and then nobody will want you.

38:36.147 --> 38:37.732
You were there, too, Amy,

38:38.817 --> 38:40.026
that day in the van.

38:52.038 --> 38:55.667
ADRIENNE: And on you is this curse
until the day of recompense.

39:08.721 --> 39:10.849
(telephone ringing)

39:11.474 --> 39:12.433
Garrison.

39:12.642 --> 39:13.601
JOE: Colin.

39:14.227 --> 39:15.270
It's Joe Saad.

39:18.231 --> 39:19.315
Been a long time.

39:21.526 --> 39:22.652
I need a favor.

39:24.779 --> 39:26.114
Not again, Joe.

39:27.282 --> 39:28.116
We're square.

39:28.700 --> 39:31.411
We'll only be square
once Sara McFetridge is found.

39:36.082 --> 39:37.000
What is it?

39:38.710 --> 39:40.128
I know who took Carrie Anderson.

39:42.171 --> 39:43.798
Carrie's been found, Joe.

39:45.133 --> 39:46.050
It's all over the news.

39:50.346 --> 39:52.974
The community of Woodfield
are rejoicing today

39:53.057 --> 39:56.352
at the discovery of missing
eight-year-old schoolgirl Carrie Anderson

39:56.436 --> 39:58.479
in the bushland of Lake Eildon.

39:58.897 --> 40:02.358
Detectives will speak to Carrie
when they get medical clearance.

40:02.567 --> 40:04.402
But they don't believe there's foul play.

40:04.485 --> 40:07.071
REPORTER: Carrie was found disoriented
and suffering severe hypothermia.

40:07.155 --> 40:08.865
It's good news, Freya.

40:09.490 --> 40:10.867
At least this one,

40:12.410 --> 40:13.620
she found her way home.

40:14.203 --> 40:15.413
FREYA: Yeah.

40:15.496 --> 40:16.706
REPORTER: ...the rain,
with temperatures dropping

40:16.789 --> 40:18.833
as low as two degrees overnight.

40:19.500 --> 40:22.712
Carrie would have had access
to the fresh water of Lake Eildon

40:22.921 --> 40:26.758
and it's possible she found shelter
in the many abandoned fishing shacks

40:26.841 --> 40:28.635
and holiday homes in the area.

40:31.262 --> 40:33.514
(foreboding music playing)

40:41.481 --> 40:43.483
WILKES: Joe, I've given you your head,

40:44.525 --> 40:47.904
but you've got no proof The Kindred
is connected to Sara's disappearance.

40:47.987 --> 40:49.489
Forensics have found no link.

40:49.572 --> 40:52.742
We get Adrienne extradited,
then we subpoena her followers.

40:52.825 --> 40:54.243
Blow this thing wide open.

40:54.327 --> 40:56.496
I need charges to extradite her.

40:56.579 --> 40:59.540
Abuse. Forgery. Kidnapping.

40:59.624 --> 41:01.876
Drug administration to minors.
What more do you want?

41:01.960 --> 41:03.419
None of it links back to her.

41:04.462 --> 41:06.631
Sara McFetridge was at their compound.

41:07.340 --> 41:08.925
Amy Beaufort confirmed it.

41:09.008 --> 41:12.261
The... The DPP will never accept charges

41:12.345 --> 41:15.515
based on the evidence
of a psychologically damaged kid.

41:15.848 --> 41:18.142
And even if they did, you can't put
traumatized kids on the stand.

41:18.226 --> 41:20.103
The defense will destroy them.

41:21.396 --> 41:24.816
Just let them move on with their lives.

41:25.274 --> 41:26.317
Leave it to Welfare.

41:26.818 --> 41:28.569
This isn't a Welfare issue.

41:29.153 --> 41:31.406
A little girl never came home

41:31.489 --> 41:35.326
and Adrienne Beaufort knows exactly
what happened to her.

41:38.371 --> 41:40.581
All right, find me a watertight charge

41:40.748 --> 41:43.001
and I'll have Interpol slap
a red notice on her.

41:43.668 --> 41:44.502
Thank you.

41:50.091 --> 41:51.384
(telephone ringing in distance)

41:52.760 --> 41:54.762
(indistinct chatter)

42:00.351 --> 42:02.562
(suspenseful music playing)

42:07.650 --> 42:09.944
-Saad.
-RECEPTIONIST: Someone here to see you.

42:14.365 --> 42:19.454
HENRIK: I confess to the kidnapping
of Sara McFetridge.

42:20.204 --> 42:24.751
I took her against her will
and I held her captive.

42:26.169 --> 42:30.173
It had nothing to do with The Kindred.

42:31.007 --> 42:32.592
There's no one else involved.

42:36.304 --> 42:39.057
Can you tell us where Sara is now?

42:39.807 --> 42:40.767
I don't know.

42:42.852 --> 42:46.105
I realize what I did was wrong,
so I drove her home.

42:46.189 --> 42:48.191
But she never came home.

42:48.274 --> 42:52.195
Well, it was late and she was asleep
so I left her on the doorstep.

42:52.528 --> 42:53.988
Why did you kidnap her, Henrik?

42:55.281 --> 42:57.200
I wanted a daughter.

42:57.658 --> 42:58.910
You mean Adrienne did.

43:00.244 --> 43:01.662
Was this her way of stealing children

43:01.746 --> 43:03.414
now that she couldn't get them
from hospitals anymore?

43:03.831 --> 43:06.667
I have given you my statement.

43:09.796 --> 43:10.880
(car door closes)

43:24.060 --> 43:26.270
(birds chirping)

43:35.029 --> 43:36.197
(knocking)

43:38.491 --> 43:39.325
You okay?

43:41.244 --> 43:43.204
You'll find Asha now, won't you?

43:48.793 --> 43:50.211
Welcome to your new home, Amy.

43:51.129 --> 43:52.380
Come on in.

43:52.463 --> 43:53.756
I'll show you your room.

44:00.429 --> 44:01.639
(door closes)

44:02.807 --> 44:04.809
(light music playing)

44:16.946 --> 44:18.781
You can help yourself
to whatever you want.

44:29.292 --> 44:30.209
Beautiful.

44:32.044 --> 44:33.296
You look good, darling.

44:35.590 --> 44:36.632
Good girl.

44:40.595 --> 44:42.889
(all laugh, chatter)

44:56.485 --> 44:57.778
(brakes screech)

45:28.017 --> 45:30.228
(bell ringing)

45:35.608 --> 45:36.776
HANNAH: You may sit.

45:41.280 --> 45:42.531
Get out!

45:43.074 --> 45:44.575
(voices echoing)

45:44.659 --> 45:48.412
YOUNG FREYA AND SARA:
One heart together, we are united...

45:54.252 --> 45:58.839
BRYCE: There are things known
and there are things unknown.

45:59.632 --> 46:00.675
The truth...

46:03.052 --> 46:04.971
lies in between.

46:05.846 --> 46:11.686
We must have the courage to open the door
to the in between.

46:13.604 --> 46:15.940
An alternate perception, as it were.

46:18.025 --> 46:22.738
Now, perhaps more than
at any other time in history,

46:23.322 --> 46:27.159
we have the opportunity to,
to look beyond what is known,

46:27.451 --> 46:29.036
and rebuild our world.

46:31.455 --> 46:33.749
SARA: Amy, help me!

46:37.420 --> 46:39.630
Help! Let me out!

46:41.716 --> 46:43.259
Let me out!

46:55.146 --> 46:57.148
(breathes deeply)

46:58.774 --> 47:01.444
Amy, help me!

47:02.236 --> 47:07.992
There is a splendor inside us
and it cannot be cowed.

47:09.827 --> 47:14.332
You must open the door
to receive the radiance.

47:14.915 --> 47:20.796
ADRIENNE: Darkness will lure us
with promises, tempt us with riches.

47:21.672 --> 47:25.217
But we must never stop seeking the light,

47:26.010 --> 47:29.013
and the grace of the unknowable truth.

47:35.936 --> 47:37.938
(closing theme music)
